            "reviews": "“Shiny reminded me of Rayman Legends, because every level looks awesome and there has been attention to create some new side scrolling tactics. Where Rayman is loud an bright colored, Shiny is calm and brings a world build out of metal to life. The developers clearly paid much attention to every detail present in the game while developing it, which really shows. I took the role of Kramer 227 without hesitation and I loved every energy-gathering and energy-spending minute of it!”<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=http://dumeegamer.com/reviews/diana/shiny.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >Dumee Gamer</a><br><br>“With breathtakingly haunting audio and some nostalgic gameplay, Shiny is a wordlessly emotional story with a sympathetic hero that has all the potential to be a great experience.”<br><a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/linkfilter/?url=http://cogconnected.com/review/shiny-review/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"  >COGConnected</a><br>",
